    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Heraclii <lb n="2"/>Dignissimo principali <lb n="3"/>innocentissimo puero <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> Flavio Vibiano Iuniori <lb n="5"/>pontifici du<expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>mviro</abbr></expan> filio ac <lb n="6"/>collegae <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> Flavi Frontini <lb n="7"/>Heraclii in parvulis annis <lb n="8"/>exhibenti aequaliter <lb n="9"/>voluptatum genera patris <lb n="10"/>sui studiis populi sufragio <lb n="11"/>et decreto ordinis </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Divina stirpe progenito <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omino</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>ostro</ex></expan> fortissimo principi <lb n="3"/>Valentiniano victori Pio <lb n="4"/>Felici ac triumphatori <lb n="5"/>semper Augusto <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avius</ex></expan> Vivius Benedictus <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>erfectissimus</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/>pr<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>eses</abbr></expan> provinciae <lb n="8"/>Tripolitanae numini <lb n="9"/>maiestatique eius <lb n="10"/>semper devotus
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>IRT 595 and 652 are the same inscription. IRT 476 was subsequently carved on the reversed face of IRT 595. Datierungen: IRT 595: spätkonstantinische Zeit; IRT 476: 378 n. Chr. (B): CIL 08, 00012, CIL 08, 22671: Z. 6: Flavius Benedictus. (B): CIL 08, 00014, CIL 08, 10994, CIL 08, 22673: Z. 5-6: filio / ac colleg(a)e, Z. 8: exibenti, Z. 10: suffragio.</p>
            </div>
